comment_data.body:
`LEAVE_LUA_ACTIVE_STATE()` is not called if the function returns here:
```c
    if (!nlua_is_deferred_safe()) {
      return luaL_error(lstate, e_fast_api_disabled, "%s");
    }
```
Additionally, is it necessary to call `ENTER_LUA_ACTIVE_STATE()` this early? I think only the actual API call may use `active_lstate`.

Also I remembered I did something else that also involves saving and restoring in <https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/32622/files#diff-a9e7b6d06d43f0fab9faeacbd587790177f028f8118d867082513193fbdb4fb4> (not all the changes there are related) by just adding the saving and restoring above and below the actual function call.

